properties.name: Mamava
properties.short_description: Mamava delivers design solutions for nursing mamas on the go, making the world a friendlier place for women to pump or breastfeed.
properties.description: Mamava is dedicated to transforming the culture of breastfeeding, making it more optimistic, realistic, accommodating, and inviting to all mamas.

properties.bio:
Sascha is Co-founder and CEO of Mamava, Inc.  Sascha started with Solidarity of Unbridled Labour (Mamava’s birthplace) in 1995. She helped to develop the Living Brand®, Solidarity’s philosophy on brands and brand creation. Before joining Solidarity, Sascha worked for the office of Congressman (now Senator) Bernard Sanders (I-Vt.), where she served as staff assistant and then assistant press secretary. 

Mamava designs solutions for nursing mamas on the go. Mama founded, women owned, and B Certified, Mamava is the leading expert in lactation spaces, integrating the biological, physical, and emotional needs of nursing mamas into both our Mamava lactation suites and our mobile app. Mamava combines beautiful design with smart lock technology to serve the needs of the twenty-first century mama on the go, revolutionizing the breastfeeding experience for traveling and working mamas, making it more optimistic, realistic, and accessible. A category creator, Mamava is working to ensure breastfeeding is a right, not a privilege.

properties.name: FreshTracks Capital
properties.short_description: FreshTracks is an early stage venture capital firm currently investing out of its 2016 vintage FreshTracks IV Fund.
properties.description: FreshTracks is a seed & early stage venture capital firm focused on financing businesses in Vermont and surrounding regions. The firm was founded in 2000, and is currently investing out of its 2016 vintage FreshTracks IV Fund, which is managed by co-founder Cairn Cross, T.J. Whalen & Lee Bouyea.  FreshTracks’ expertise, networks, resources and capital support innovative businesses through multiple rounds of financing and stages of growth.
